# 🛠️ Built Process - Custom Virtual File System (VFS)

## 📌 Overview
This folder contains the step-by-step development of the **Custom Virtual File System (VFS)** project.  
Each file represents incremental progress made while building the final system.

---

## 🚀 Purpose
- Track the complete development journey  
- Understand feature-by-feature implementation  
- Showcase problem-solving and iterative development approach  

---

## 📂 Structure

Each file corresponds to a specific development stage:

step1_create_file.cpp      → Basic file creation logic  
step2_read_file.cpp        → File reading implementation  
step3_write_file.cpp       → Writing data to files  
step4_delete_file.cpp      → File deletion logic  
step5_directory.cpp        → Directory handling  
...

---

## ⚙️ Development Approach

The project was built using a structured, step-by-step approach:

1. Started with basic file operations  
2. Incrementally added new features  
3. Tested each module independently  
4. Integrated all features into a final system  

👉 Final working implementation:
src/main.cpp

---

## 🧠 Key Learnings

- File system design fundamentals  
- Memory management using C-style programming  
- Implementation of core file operations  
- Importance of incremental development  

